  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: There is no explanation in iOS Settings why Status app needs a location access. The explanation maybe necessary before submitting the app to AppStore. It also builds confidence. \r\nHere is a Chrome app example: \"Get a better experience in Chrome based on your location.\"\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nThere is an \"App explanation\" in Location Settings. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\"App explanation\" is empty:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/34742178-98ef848e-f585-11e7-9fc6-0be7721ce6d1.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Settings app on iOS \r\n- Find Status app and open it\r\n- Go to Location options\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.12 (TestFlight)\r\n* Operating System: iOS 11.2.1",
